Data Privacy Framework Notice
Scope of this privacy notice
This Privacy Notice explains how Viasat collects, uses, discloses or otherwise processes your personal data when you use our websites and when we provide many of our services to you. We also explain your data protection rights as well as how to contact us if you have questions or comments.
Viasat collects your personal information when you interact with us.  We respect your privacy, and for this reason we work hard to gain and maintain your trust and to be transparent about how we use your information.  This Privacy Notice explains who we are, how we collect, use, and share your personal data and your related rights.
This Privacy Notice applies to the personal data that we collect when you visit the Viasat websites including when you sign up to any newsletters, download content, register for events or webinars (“
Websites
”); take part in competitions; purchase or use our residential, commercial, and community broadband connectivity, communications, content and analytics services; engage with our mobile applications (“
Apps
”); contact our customer support agents; receive and interact with the communications we send to you; or otherwise engage or communicate with us related to any of these services, or any other Viasat products or services that link to this Privacy Notice  (collectively referred to as the “
Services
”).
We may provide these Services to you directly, such as when you sign up for our residential satellite broadband service.  You also may access certain Services because Viasat has a relationship with your company and we collect certain information about you as a result, including your user contact information and username and password credentials that enable you to access and use our Services, such as our Intelie by Viasat services.
IMPORTANT
:  Viasat collects personal data for different reasons, not all of which are addressed in this Privacy Notice.  For example, the personal data processing for Viasat’s Mobility services, including our
in-flight connectivity, maritime, and related services,
is covered under a separate Privacy Notice.  Also, we collect personal data from you if you
apply for employment with Viasat
, and the processing of your information in this context is covered under a different Privacy Notice.  Our other privacy notices can be found in the Privacy Center on our Websites or at other locations where you interact with us.
Where we refer to “Viasat” (or “
us
,” “
we,
” or “
our
”) in this Privacy Notice, we mean Viasat, Inc., Inmarsat Global Limited and all of our group companies. To find information on the group company that is the owner of a particular Website or provider (or data controller) of a particular service, you can find a list of those entities
here
. If you have any questions or comments about our use of your personal data, please contact us using the contact details provided at the bottom of this Privacy Notice.
We recommend that you read this entire Privacy Notice so that you are fully informed about how we treat your personal data and your rights. This includes information available in the “
Service-Specific Privacy Information
” and “
Additional Information Based on Your Location
” sections of this Notice that include details on our personal data processing that apply depending on the specific Viasat service you use, or your location,
e.g.
, state, country, or region.
Who we are and what we do
Viasat, including Inmarsat has been providing consumers, businesses and enterprises in the aviation, maritime, and other sections, and governments with communications and broadband internet products and services for more than 40 years.
Viasat is a global communications provider headquartered in the United States. Viasat group of companies are located throughout the world. You can find a list of many of our Viasat locations on our website
here
.
Personal data we collect and sources of information
The personal data we collect either directly or indirectly from or about you will depend on the Service you are using and how you interact with us, and can include your contact, payment and service details, device information, websites you visit, cookies, and data captured using other tracking technologies.
When you interact with Viasat, we collect personal data about you from the following different sources:
Directly from you.
We collect personal data such as your name and contact information directly from you when you voluntarily choose to provide us with this information.
Indirectly.
We collect personal data about you indirectly, including through automated means.  Data we collect indirectly is captured through your use of the Services, and some information is collected using cookies and other tracking technologies, as explained further in the
“
Cookies and Similar Tracking Technology
”
section of this Notice.
Third parties.
We also collect information about you from third-party sources such as our business partners, as well as service providers that provide marketing, analytics, data (including advertising networks data), and financial and credit related services. Some of this collection may occur even before your initial interaction with us.
The table below describes the personal data we collect from and about you depending on the Service, some of which we combine in our systems.
