How we use your personal data and our legal bases
We use your personal data for various reasons, including to provide, support, and improve the Services and tailor the Services to you, to keep your information secure, and to communicate with you about the Services. We are a global company, and in certain countries and regions where we operate, we must inform you of our specific legal basis to collect and use your personal data.
We use the personal data that we collect from and about you only for the purposes described in this Privacy Notice or for purposes that we explain to you at the time we collect your information.
Laws in certain locations where we operate require that we disclose our legal basis for processing your personal data, which includes the following bases depending on which service you use:
Contract
– we require certain personal data to provide and support the Services you purchase or request from us
Consent
– in certain circumstances, we may ask for your consent before we will collect, use, or disclose your personal data, in which case you can voluntarily choose to give or deny your consent without negative consequences to you
Legitimate Interests
– we may use or disclose your personal data for the legitimate business interests of either Viasat or a third party, but only when we’re confident that your privacy rights will remain appropriately protected
Legal Obligation
– there may be instances where we must process and retain your information to comply with laws or to fulfill certain legal obligations
Vital Interests
– there may be circumstances where we will process your information to protect your vital interests or those of another person
If we rely on our (or a third party’s) legitimate interests to collect and use your personal data, these interests will normally be to operate and provide our Services, communicate with you and respond to your questions, improve our Services or use the insights to improve or develop new services, market or promote either our Services or the services of a third-party that are closely partnered with our Services, or to detect or prevent illegal activities.
Where we need to collect personal data by law, or under the terms of a contract we have with you and you fail to provide that data when requested, we may not be able to perform the contract we have or are trying to enter into with you (for example, to provide you with goods or services). In this case, we may have to cancel a product or service you have with us but we will notify you if this is the case at the time.
