When we share your personal data
Your information may be shared with third parties, such as service providers (within and outside the Viasat group) and business partners. On certain occasions where necessary or required, we may share your information with law enforcement, government agencies, or the purchasers of some or all of a Viasat group business.
We may disclose your personal data to the following categories of recipients to the extent permitted by applicable law:
Viasat group companies.
We share information across the Viasat and Inmarsat group companies to help us operate our business and Services or for their own purposes, such as to provide their services directly to you.  These entities are located in various countries around the world.  A list of countries in which Viasat entities are located can be found
here
. If a group company uses your information for its own purposes, those entities are ‘controllers’ (or a similar-meaning term) of your personal data. We sometimes may share information with group companies in an aggregated and anonymized format and in those cases, you will not be identified through the information that is disclosed.  Generally, all categories of the personal data that we process will be accessible to Viasat, Inc.
Third-party service providers.
We use third-party vendors to perform services on our behalf.  These vendors provide business, professional, payment processing, marketing and advertising, analytics and measurement, and technical and hosting support to us, help us operate our business, Services, and Websites, and administer activities in support of our business and the Services on our behalf.  These vendors range from consulting services provided by groups and individuals, large technology platform and cloud hosting providers like Amazon Web Services, Salesforce, SAP, and others, and other third-party technology application providers.  These vendors are not permitted by us to use or share your personal data for either their own or another third party’s commercial purposes. These third parties are located in various countries around the world.
Credit agencies or bureaus.
We engage with credit agencies or bureaus to carry out credit checks so that we can make credit and solvency decisions when you request the Services. These credit agencies/bureaus are in various countries around the world.
Authorized retailers and distributors and delivery partners.
We engage with select retailers that can help you select the best Service plan for you and support installation.
You can search for our authorized retailers
here
and
here
.
Third-party ad platforms or networks.
We may also share personal data with advertising platforms or networks or permit these partners to collect information from you directly on the Websites to facilitate online advertising for Viasat services, such as search engines and social network advertising providers to serve ads for our Services to you or to groups of other users similar to you based on commercial interests and demographics, on third-party platforms or other websites you visit. For more information, including how to opt out of targeted online advertising, please visit the “
Cookies and Similar Tracking Technologies
”
section of this Privacy Notice.
Entities involved in corporate transaction.
We may sell or purchase assets during the normal course of our business.  In connection with these transactions, we may disclose your personal data or transfer this information to another entity as part of a potential or actual acquisition or merger of Viasat or any portion of our assets. If we bring or are defending a reorganization, bankruptcy, or similar event, your personal data may be considered our asset and sold or transferred to third parties. These third parties are located in various countries around the world.
Law enforcement, governmental, judicial and related entities
.  We may share your information to protect the security of our Services, network, and IT systems and applications, and business and in connection with an investigation of fraud, intellectual property infringements, interference with our rights, property or users, or other activity that is illegal or may expose you or us to legal liability, including as required or requested by outside auditors or advisors, law enforcement or other government officials.  We also may share your information with third parties when we have reason to believe that a disclosure is necessary to address potential or actual injury or interference with our rights, property, operations, users, or others who may be harmed or may suffer loss or damage. We may share your information when we believe that it is necessary to protect our rights, investigate, or enforce our policies, terms or other legal document or contract, or to comply with a judicial proceeding, court order, or legal process served on Viasat. We may share your data with public authorities such as tax authorities, to comply with our legal obligations.
Other persons with your consent
to the disclosure.
Third parties who receive aggregate or anonymous information.
We may share aggregate or anonymous information with third parties, including our business partners, for their business, marketing, or analytics uses. When we do, we take steps to ensure that this information cannot be used to identify you.
Cookies and similar tracking technology
Cookies are small data files that are placed on your computer or mobile device when you visit a website or online platform.  We use cookies and similar tracking technology (collectively, “
Cookies
”) to operate and enhance our Websites and certain Services and understand how you navigate our Websites and Services, to maintain user preferences or settings, combat fraud, help to ensure compliance with our policies and Terms of Use, and support our online advertising (including retargeting efforts) for Viasat services.  Where required by applicable law, we ask you to provide your consent to or give you choices on the use of these tracking technologies.
For more information about the types of Cookies we use, why, and how you can control Cookies, please see either our Cookie Notice or the Do Not Sell or Share My Personal Information page available on the Website or Service you are using.
How we secure your personal data
Viasat takes the security of your personal data seriously. The measures we use to protect your information may vary between Websites and the Services.
We take our responsibility to protect your information seriously and use appropriate technical, physical, and organizational measures to safeguard the information that we process through our Websites and Services. The measures we use are designed to provide a level of security appropriate to the risk of processing your personal data. No security system is 100% secure, however, and we cannot guarantee our security measures will not be compromised.;
International data transfers
We operate as a global organization with service providers and partners around the world. Your personal data may be transferred to countries with data protection standards that are not equal to the standards in the country where you are located. We put in place appropriate measures to safeguard your personal data when transferring it around the world.
Your personal data may be transferred to, and processed in, countries other than the country in which you reside.  These countries may have data protection laws that are different than the laws of your country (and, in some cases, may not be as protective).
The servers that operate or process personal data related to our Services are primarily located in the United States and the UK, though personal data also may be transferred to India, Israel, Ireland, and the group countries in which our business is established or our Services are available, and potentially other countries. Our group companies and third-party service providers and partners operate around the world. This means that when we collect your personal data, we or our service providers may process it in any of these countries. Please see under the heading "
When We Share Your Personal Data
" above for further information on third parties we may share your personal data with and in which countries they are located.
We take appropriate safeguards to help ensure that your personal data remains protected in accordance with this Privacy Notice. These include, for example, implementing the UK and European Commission’s Standard Contractual Clauses for transfers of personal data between our group companies, which require all group companies to protect personal data they process from the European Economic Area, Switzerland and the UK in accordance with data protection laws in those areas. Where appropriate, we also put in place additional safeguards to protect your personal data when it is transferred to countries considered to be less protective.
Information on the Standard Contractual Clauses we have in place between our Viasat group companies can be provided on request.  We have implemented similar appropriate safeguards with our third-party service providers and partners.
We may also use the Data Privacy Framework for certain transfers of personal data from the European Economic Area (EEA), the United Kingdom (UK) and Switzerland to the United States. Please see our
Data Privacy Framework Notice
for more information.
Additional region-specific information
Data protection laws and requirements can differ by location, including region, country, or state. Where appropriate, we describe additional country specific information about our collection and use of your personal data in connection with our Websites and  Services.
If you are in one of the locations listed below, please click on the relevant link for country specific information about our collection and use of your personal data.
United States
(including state-specific information, e.g.,
CA
,
ME
,
NV
)
UK, Switzerland and European Union Economic Area
Brazil
Mexico
How long we keep your information
We will keep your personal data for as long as we have a legitimate business need to do so.
We retain the personal data we collect from you where we have an ongoing legitimate purpose to do so described in the “
How We Use Your Personal Data and Our Legal Bases
” section above. For example, where we process your information based on a contract with you, we generally will retain the information for the length of the contract to provide you with a service you have requested or to comply with applicable legal, tax or accounting requirements).
When we no longer have an ongoing legitimate business need to process your personal data, we will either delete or anonymize it or, if this is not possible (for example, because your personal data has been stored in backup archives), then we will securely store your personal data and isolate it from any further processing until deletion is possible.
Automated decision-making
We do not use your personal data to engage in automated decision-making that will have a significant effect on you (legally or otherwise).  In the U.S., we use automated tools that process information such as your location and credit history to assess whether our Services are an available or most appropriate service option for you and to inform the appropriate initial upfront fee for our Services.
Your choices and data protection rights
Depending on your location, you may have certain rights that you can exercise over our collection and use of your personal data.
Depending on your location, the privacy laws that apply to Viasat and our Services give you certain rights over the personal data we process about you.  These rights are in addition to your right to know or be informed about how we process your data, which we honor through our descriptions in this Privacy Notice.  Your data protection rights may include:
You can
access, correct, update or request deletion
of your personal data.  You also can
object to processing
of your personal data, ask us to
restrict processing
of your personal data or
request portability
of your personal data.  You can exercise these rights at any time by submitting a request through our online
Privacy Rights Request Form
.  You also have the right to
avoid discrimination
by us in response to exercising your rights.
You have the right to
opt-out of marketing communications
we send you at any time.  You can exercise this right by clicking on the “unsubscribe” or “opt-out” link in the marketing e-mails you receive from us.  To opt-out of other forms of marketing (such as postal marketing or telemarketing), please contact us using the contact details provided under the “
How to Contact Us
” heading below.
If we have collected and process your personal data with your consent, then you can
withdraw your consent
at any time.  Withdrawing your consent will not affect the lawfulness of our processing activity prior to your withdrawal, nor will it affect our processing of your personal data conducted in reliance on lawful processing grounds other than consent.
You have the
right to complain to a data protection authority
about our collection and use of your personal data.  For more information, please contact your local data protection authority.
Privacy controls
Requests to exercise your data protection rights
Please submit a request using our
Privacy Rights Request Form
to exercise your data protection rights. While your location determines what rights are available to you, we respond to all requests we receive from individuals wishing to exercise their data protection rights in accordance with applicable data protection laws.
Requests to stop sending directed marketing
You can unsubscribe from marketing emails by clicking the unsubscribe link at the bottom of the email you receive from Viasat or its marketing partner. You also can use our
Privacy Rights Request Form
to instruct us to remove you from our marketing campaigns.
Account management
If you have set up an online account for Services that is accessible through one of our Websites or Apps you can manage your account settings by logging into your account.
For management of online accounts you have set up in connection with the Services, you can manage settings from within your account.
Accepting or rejecting Cookies
You can change cookie settings (including to decline non-essential cookies) by visiting our Cookie Notice or the Do Not Sell or Share my Personal Information page available on the Viasat Websites or Services you are using (where applicable based on local laws)
.
You can also adjust your browser settings more generally and modify local device settings to accept or reject cookies. For more information on how to do this, please see our Cookie Notice available on the applicable Website or Service.
Personal data about children
Viasat Websites and Services are not intended to be used by children.  We do not intentionally collect children's data.
The Viasat Websites and Services are not directed to children under 13 years old (or older, if applicable law provides for different protections), and we do not intentionally collect personal data from children. If you become aware that we have inadvertently collected personal data from a child, please notify us as soon as possible by contacting us using the contact details provided under the “
How to Contact Us
” heading below.
Updates to this Privacy Notice
We may update this Privacy Notice from time to time in response to changing business, technical or legal developments. When we update our Privacy Notice, we take appropriate measures to inform you and provide you with appropriate choice, consistent with the significance of the changes we make, and in compliance with applicable data protection laws.
You can see when this Privacy Notice was last updated by checking the “last updated” date displayed at the top of this Privacy Notice.
How to contact us
If you have any questions or concerns about our use of your personal information, please contact us using the following details:
Viasat, Inc.
Attn:  Viasat Privacy Office (Legal Dept.)
901 K Street, NW, Suite 400
Washington, DC 20001
Email: privacy@viasat.com
